Lagos – Ex-international, Taiwo Oloyede has charged Al-Hilal striker, Odion Ighalo to re-enact his club’s form with the Super Eagles when they play Black Stars of Ghana in the World Cup Playoffs later this month. “Ighalo is doing very well at the club and he has proved that he can be relied upon when called up. “I want to charge him to keep up the tempo and use experience to help the Super Eagles against Black Stars,” said Oloyede. Brume Leads Team Nigeria To Belgrade For World Athletics Indoor… United Kingdom Government To Sell Chelsea Football Club According to him, Ighalo can make the difference in the playoffs and give Nigeria the World Cup ticket. It will be recalled that Ighalo scored his 16th league goal of the season in the Saudi Arabia league to help Al-Hilal secure a 2-1 win against league leaders Al-Ittihad FC on Tuesday. His goal scoring form and experience were the likely considerations for his inclusion in Nigeria’s 2022 World Cup playoff ties against Ghana.